{{Orphan|date=June 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox scientist | name = Ajit Johnson | image = Ajit Johnson Nirmal.jpg | caption = Johnson at the [[Intelligent Systems for Molecular Biology]] conference in 2015 | birth_place = [[Chennai]], India | residence = [[Boston]], USA | workplaces = [[Harvard University]], [[Dana–Farber Cancer Institute]] | alma_mater = {{plainlist| * [[University College London]] * [[University of Edinburgh]] }} | known_for = {{hlist|[[Computational Biology]]|[[Bioinformatics]]|[[Oncogenomics]]}} | website = {{url|http://www.ajitjohnson.com}} }}
'''Ajit Johnson''' is a cancer geneticist. He has also campaigned to raise awareness on tech addiction and [[net neutrality]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/declancashin/talkin-bout-my-generation#.yhNNMQm2J|title=These Posters Perfectly Sum Up Twentysomethings' Addiction to the Internet|last1=Cashin|first1=Declan|publisher=BuzzFeed}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/mckenna-bulkley/the-truth-about-thisgeneration_b_7056844.html|title=The Truth About #ThisGeneration|last1=Bulkley|first1=McKenna|publisher=www.huffingtonpost.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://madovermarketing.com/2015/04/14/these-creatives-supporting-net-neutrality-will-make-you-go-save-the-internet/|title=These Creatives Supporting Net Neutrality Will Make You Go Save The Internet!|publisher=Mad Over Marketing|agency=http://madovermarketing.com/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://storycurry.com/these-13-witty-protests-to-safeguard-net-neutrality-will-surely-prove-that-when-it-comes-to-protests-we-indians-just-became-so-much-more-cooler/|title=These 13 Witty Protests To Safeguard Net Neutrality Will Surely Prove That When It Comes To Protests, We Indians Just Became So Much More Cooler|work=storycurry.com/|agency=Story Curry}}</ref>
== Early life == Born in [[Vellore]], Johnson graduated with a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[biotechnology]] at [[Karunya University]]. At the age of 10, he started making art. He said, "Being able to tell stories through my art that promotes social awareness, love, hope and encouragement is something I love."<ref>{{cite news|title = this generation satirical posters|url = http://www.boredpanda.com/this-generation-satirical-posters-ajit-johnson/}}</ref>
==Career==
=== Education === Johnson graduated from [[University College London]] in 2011 and worked at the [[Indian Institute of Science]]. In 2012, he moved to [[Singapore]] to work at the [[National Cancer Centre]] where he developed a cell based [[gene therapy]] for [[haemophilia]] patients.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Nirmal|first1=Ajit Johnson|title=Peptide vaccine therapy in colorectal cancer|journal=Vaccines|date=2013|volume=1|issue=1|page=1|url=http://www.mdpi.com/2076-393X/1/1/1}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=ImSig: Conserved immune cell signature for deconvolution of complex blood and tissue transcriptomic data|journal=F1000Research|date=2015|issue=4(ISCB Comm J):394|pages=|doi= 10.7490/f1000research.1110149.1}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Cell-cycle analysis and micronuclei frequency reveals G0/G1 blockers as weak micronuclei inducers|journal=Drug and Chemical Toxicology|date=2013|volume=36|issue=2|pages=249–254|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.3109/01480545.2012.737803|doi=10.3109/01480545.2012.737803}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=P59. The mechanogrowth factor expression in colorectal cancer: A potential new target for nanoparticles|journal=European Journal of Surgical Oncology|date=2012|volume=38|issue=11|pages=1122|url=https://www.infona.pl/resource/bwmeta1.element.elsevier-7078c2f1-0fc5-3fb2-a2da-214a0e4ce03e|doi=10.1016/j.ejso.2012.07.180}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=The role of autophagy in colorectal cancer cells: A pro-survival mechanism|journal=European Journal of Surgical Oncology|date=2012|volume=38|issue=11|pages=1120|doi=10.1016/j.ejso.2012.07.173}}</ref> In 2018 he earned a Doctor of Philosophy in cancer [[genetics]] and [[genomics]] from the [[University of Edinburgh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=University of Edinburgh: The Roslin Institute|url=http://www.roslin.ed.ac.uk/tom-freeman/group-members/}}</ref>
=== Research === Johnson focuses on understanding the differences in molecular signature of immune cells across [[tumours]]. He uses large cancer datasets to identify, characterize and model [[immune system]] across different tumour types. He developed ''ImSig'', the network-based computational framework that facilitates the characterization of immune cells within the tumor microenvironment.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nirmal|first=Ajit J.|last2=Regan|first2=Tim|last3=Shih|first3=Barbara B.|last4=Hume|first4=David A.|last5=Sims|first5=Andrew H.|last6=Freeman|first6=Tom C.|date=2018-09-28|title=Immune Cell Gene Signatures for Profiling the Microenvironment of Solid Tumors|url=http://cancerimmunolres.aacrjournals.org/content/early/2018/10/22/2326-6066.CIR-18-0342|journal=Cancer Immunology Research|language=en|doi=10.1158/2326-6066.CIR-18-0342|issn=2326-6066|pmid=30266715}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Nirmal|first=Ajit Johnson|title=imsig: Immune Cell Gene Signatures for Profiling the Microenvironment of Solid Tumours|date=2018-07-10|url=https://cran.r-project.org/package=imsig|volume=|pages=|access-date=2018-10-25}}</ref> His work involves an extensive degree of both experimental and computational based analysis.<ref>{{cite journal|title=ImSig: Conserved immune cell signature for [[deconvolution]] of complex blood and tissue transcriptomic data|journal=F1000Research|date=2015|issue=4(ISCB Comm J):394|pages=|doi=10.7490/f1000research.1110149.1}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=University of Edinburgh Group Pages|url=http://www.roslin.ed.ac.uk/tom-freeman/group-members/}}</ref>
