{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}
{{Use British English|date=May 2015}}
Dr. '''Alan Keith Huggins''' (born May 1936) [[Members of the Order of the British Empire|MBE]] is a [[philatelist]] who in 1981, with [[Marcus Samuel (philatelist)|Marcus Samuel]], was awarded the [[Crawford Medal]] for his work ''Specimen stamps and stationery of Great Britain''.<ref>''The Society's medals and honorary fellowship''. The Royal Philatelic Society London, 2009, p. 4.</ref>

In 1994 he was awarded the [[Lichtenstein Medal]].

In the January 1996 [[New Year Honours]] list, Huggins was honoured with the award of Membership of the Order of the British Empire for services to the [[British Philatelic Trust]]. This was the first occasion this honour was given within philately, other than those awarded directly by the monarch to the Keeper of the [[Royal Philatelic Collection]].<ref>The London Philatelist, No 1232, p.1, Jan/Feb 1996</ref>

Huggins is a past President of the [[Royal Philatelic Society London]] and also a past Chairman of The [[Postal Stationery Society]] (1992 - 1999).

==Selected publications==
*''British Postal Stationery'', Great Britain Philatelic Society, London, 1970
*''Specimen stamps and stationery of Great Britain.'' Safron Walden: G.B. Philatelic Publications Ltd., 1980. (With Marcus Samuel)
*''Collect British Postal Stationery'', GB Philatelic Publications Ltd, 2007. {{ISBN|978-0-907630-22-7}} (with Colin Baker)

