'''Alija Gušanac''' ("Alija from Gusinje"; {{floruit}} 1804–05), known in epic poetry as '''Gušanac-Alija''', was an Ottoman [[brigand]] (''krdžalija'') that served the ''[[Dahije]]'', the renegade [[Janissaries]] that had taken the rule of the [[Sanjak of Smederevo]] following a coup. He was from [[Gusinje]], hence his byname. At the start of the Serbian uprising against the Dahije (1804), Gušanac was in [[Jagodina]]. He was subsequently appointed commander of Belgrade by the Dahije.

