{{Notability|Academics|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox philosopher |region = [[American philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy]] |name = Bradley Dowden |image = |birth_date = |birth_place = |school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy]] |main_interests = [[Philosophy of science]], [[metaphysics]], [[philosophy of mind]], [[logic]] |notable_ideas = |influences = |influenced = }}
'''Bradley Harris Dowden''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|d|aʊ|d|ən}}) is professor of [[philosophy]] at the [[California State University, Sacramento]].
==Work== He is a general editor of the [[Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy]]. Dowden received his MS in [[physics]] from [[Ohio State University]] and his PhD in philosophy from [[Stanford University]].<ref>[http://www.csus.edu/phil/Department/Faculty/Dowden.html Bradley Dowden] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150112133355/http://www.csus.edu/phil/Department/Faculty/Dowden.html |date=January 12, 2015 }}</ref> His main interests are [[metaphysics]], [[philosophy of science]], [[philosophy of mind]], [[logic]], [[time]], [[paradox]] and [[infinity]].<ref>[https://www.sfu.ca/~swartz/dowden/logical_reasoning.htm Review of Bradley H. Dowden's Logical Reasoning] by [[Norman Swartz]]</ref><ref>[http://www.bookdepository.com/Metaphysics-Time-Bradley-Dowden/9780742560307 The Metaphysics of Time: A Dialogue]</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Dowden-Swartz Exchange | url=https://www.sfu.ca/~swartz/time_travel1.htm}}</ref>
