{{COI|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox person |birth_name = |name = Jennifer Stefano |image = |birth_date = |birth_place = |residence = |ethnicity = |occupation = Reporter, activist |alma_mater = [[Villanova University]] |children = |website = [http://jenniferstefano.com/ www.jenniferstefano.com] }}
'''Jennifer Stafano''' is a Republican activist and the Vice President for [[Americans for Prosperity|Americans for Prosperity and Americans for Prosperity Foundation]], a conservative organization that is the primary political group of the Koch brothers ([[Charles Koch]] and [[David Koch]]).
==Biography== Stefano, a recent mother and 2004 [[Emmy Award|Emmy]]-nominated reporter, felt disenfranchised by politics in 2008 when she discovered the nascent Tea Party at a local rally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://inthesetimes.com/article/6439/tea_party_confidential|title=Tea Party Confidential|first=Kate|last=Zernike|date=17 September 2010|accessdate=9 May 2018|publisher=In These Times}}</ref> She would eventually rise through the ranks of the Tea Party. Reflecting her rise in prominence in conservative circles, Stefano spoke at a panel in 2011 at [[Conservative Political Action Conference|CPAC]], Washington's biggest gathering of conservatives,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/02/21/why-is-facebook-helping-fund-cpac|title=Why Is Facebook Helping Fund CPAC?|first=Betsy|last=Woodruff|date=22 February 2017|accessdate=9 May 2018|website=Thedailybeast.com}}</ref> on a panel organized by the [[Tea Party Express]], an organizing group founded by Republican consultants.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Berry |first1=Jeffrey|last2=Sobieraj |first2=Sarah |date=2013 |title=The Outrage Industry: Political Opinion Media and the New Incivility}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teapartyexpress.org/3453/cpac-the-tea-party-visits-dc|title=CPAC – The Tea Party Visits DC - Tea Party Express|website=Teapartyexpress.org|accessdate=9 May 2018}}</ref> She became a frequent guest on Fox.<ref name="wordpress.com">{{cite web|url=https://jenniferstefano.wordpress.com/about/|title=Get to know Jennifer Stefano|date=30 December 2011|website=Jenniferstefano.wordpress.com|accessdate=9 May 2018}}</ref> Stefano eventually became the Pennsylvania State Director for [[Americans for Prosperity|AFP]].,<ref name="americansforprosperity.org">[http://americansforprosperity.org/about/staff/about-jennifer-stefano] {{dead link|date=May 2018}}</ref> the principal political arm of the Koch brothers' network.
==Media appearances== Stefano has appeared on several broadcast and cable networks as a host and commentator, and she is a "regular guest on Fox News and Fox Business News"<ref name="wordpress.com"/> <ref name="americansforprosperity.org"/> She gained widespread media attention in a confrontation with [[Bob Beckel]] on the [[Hannity]] Show on April 16, 2012. After Stefano stated that the [[Head Start Program]], which provides safety net assistance to poor children, did not work, Beckel replied, "You don't know what the f*ck you're talking about!" Beckel did not realize the show was back from the commercial break, and initially refused to apologize. When persuaded that the show was, in fact, live, Beckel apologized for his choice of language, but stood by the overall intent of the statement.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/04/17/fox-news-bob-beckel-f-bomb_n_1430863.html Fox News' Bob Beckel Drops F-Bomb On Air] The Huffington Post. April 17, 2012.</ref> Beckel's praise for Head Start was supported by education expert Valerie Strauss, who said in response to the Fox segment, "Head Start produces modest benefits including some long-term gains for children."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/answer-sheet/wp/2013/03/05/does-head-start-work-for-kids-the-bottom-line/|title=Does Head Start work for kids? The bottom line|first=Valerie|last=Strauss|date=5 March 2013|accessdate=9 May 2018|website=Washingtonpost.com}}</ref>
