[[File:Blason-Florac.svg|thumb|right|250px|Coat of arms of Earl of Sutherland]]
'''William de Moravia''' (also known as '''William Sutherland'''<ref name="Gordon1">[[Sir Robert Gordon, 1st Baronet|Gordon, Sir Robert]] (1580–1656), ''A Genealogical History of the Earldom of Sutherland''. Originally written between 1615 and 1630, published in 1813. Pages 33–44.</ref>) (fl. early 14th century) was the 3rd [[Earl of Sutherland]] and chief of [[Clan Sutherland]].

He was a signatory to the [[Declaration of Arbroath]] and died in 1325 around the age of 80.<ref>{{cite book|last=Chalmers|first=George|title=Caledonia: Or, an Account, Historical and Topographic, of North Britain|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sL8_AAAAcAAJ&pg=PA607|year=1807|publisher=Constable|pages=606–7}}</ref>

